The article is a transcript of a press briefing by White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs. Gibbs answers questions about various topics including the arrest of suspected Russian spies, General McChrystal's retirement, financial reform, climate change, immigration, and the Gulf oil spill. He also addresses concerns about Russia spying on the US and the President's support for Elena Kagan's Supreme Court nomination. Gibbs does not provide definitive answers on some questions and defers to other departments for certain topics.